### **Transcript**
AI cites benchmark studies only when users ask questions that require measurable comparisons.
After analyzing Gauge's AI citation data, benchmark reports were most frequently cited in industries where buyers compare measurable factors such as speed, cost, latency, yield, or performance—including cloud data warehouses, crypto staking, and MEV.
In contrast, industries like B2B SaaS, CRM, TEFL education, and product analytics rarely received AI citations for original research. Instead, AI preferred listicles, product pages, and explanatory content.
Key takeaway: Before investing in original research or a benchmark report, make sure your topic answers a genuine "which is better?" question backed by measurable data. Without a meaningful comparison, AI has little reason to reference your research.
The greatest opportunity lies in industries where buyers seek objective comparisons, but no credible benchmark data currently exists.
